ACCORDING to a new survey, men are not the only ones hungry for sex. The survey, conducted by dating site IllicitEncounters, revealed nearly half of women craved sex more than their lovers. At least 2 000 people were surveyed and it was found that 43% of women wanted more sex than their partners offered, while 42% of men said they wanted more action. It was also found that in 62% of break-ups, sex was a contributing factor. SunReaders were asked on Facebook whether they agreed.